CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 7, 1956, pg. A14 reads: "Modern Explorers - Sequoyah Payne, Richard Kipp and Glenn Zellers (seated), of the Bureau of Mines, enjoy basic research-the most important phase of the discovery and perfection of scientific marvels. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Three men, from left: Sequoyah Payne, Richard Kipp, and Glenn Zellers, posed in shop in the Bureau of Mines office
